{"TopicId":170269,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Bad science in fiction Hall of Shame","CreatedByName":"peadar1987","CreatedById":81207,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-30T15:01:50Z","PageNum":70,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-29T06:25:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust the Star Trek is a galactic authorities\u0027 propaganda. They don\u0027t show us what they do to the non-terrestrial worlds, following the principle \u0022who sapient would live there?\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-29T06:41:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223710968\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221574982074\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022102579\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Treveli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Treveli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve taken it as being Starfleet mission assignments.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would cover the ships being sent to known systems, but it doesn\u0027t explain the extremely high percentage of uncharted, never-before-seen planets the ships come across that just happen to be Class M.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-29T09:37:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711137\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575009679\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would cover the ships being sent to known systems, but it doesn\u0027t explain the extremely high percentage of uncharted, never-before-seen planets the ships come across that just happen to be Class M.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose planets are used for them who asks too much, why only terrestrial planets are considered inhabited.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-29T10:57:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223710968\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221574982074\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022102579\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Treveli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, Treveli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRL reason; easier on the FX budget to fill the galaxy with Earth-like worlds.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually it\u0027s more like the show - or any other sci-fi tv show since - wouldn\u0027t exist otherwise.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMcCoy\u0027s hand-held medical scanners were SALT AND PEPPER SHAKERS fercrhrissakes, and you want airless planets?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-11-29T10:58:25Z\u0022 title=\u002211/29/2019 10:58  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 29, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by 5thHorseman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KSK","CreatedById":61025,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-29T14:05:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711182\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575025079\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually it\u0027s more like the show - or any other sci-fi tv show since - wouldn\u0027t exist otherwise.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMcCoy\u0027s hand-held medical scanners were SALT AND PEPPER SHAKERS fercrhrissakes, and you want airless planets?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah. \u201CCaptain, scanners indicate that we\u2019ve located the 3127th ball of rock, ices and not-even-prebiotic organic molecules, for this mission.\u00A0The away team are reporting that their brief and pointless EVA has consumed 125% of the budget for this episode.\u201D\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-11-29T14:05:59Z\u0022 title=\u002211/29/2019 02:05  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 29, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by KSK\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-29T16:46:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet me remind to all that the Star Trek cruiser is called \u003Cem\u003EEnterprise\u003C/em\u003E...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Business\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EEnterprise\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/em\u003E. Not \u003Cem\u003EPhilanthropy\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-11-29T16:49:21Z\u0022 title=\u002211/29/2019 04:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 29, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-29T21:25:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223710936\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221574974364\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183830\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RealKerbal3x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/28/2019 at 11:52 PM, RealKerbal3x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u2019ve never posted about\u00A0Star Trek here because it\u2019s so far removed from actual science\u00A0that I don\u2019t see any reason to connect it to reality, but there\u2019s one thing that annoys me more than it really should.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n99% of the planets they visit are Earth-like, with a nice oxygen-nitrogen atmosphere and 1G gravity. Sure, Starfleet may mostly be interested in these types of planets (probably for colonisation), but surely they can\u2019t be THAT common. We only rarely see them visiting gas giants or atmosphereless rocky planets/moons, which is actually what they would likely be doing most of the time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen again, this is Star Trek, so I probably shouldn\u2019t question it... \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA theory: with easy FTL, non-Earthlike planets become utter flyover country.\u00A0 \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spacescifi","CreatedById":197504,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-29T21:52:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711365\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575062711\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA theory: with easy FTL, non-Earthlike planets become utter flyover country.\u00A0 \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReasons to colonize no-man\u0027s land when Earth-worlds and FTL warp exist are:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Your terraforming is THAT good.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. Strategic. If at war with Earth, colonizing Proxima Centauri planets is a good base of operations to launch supplies from.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. Trade operations. Sometimes some systems really do have a surplus of valuable ore. Maybe there are shiny planets with so much gold dust in the dirt that it shines from space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-11-29T21:52:25Z\u0022 title=\u002211/29/2019 09:52  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 29, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Spacescifi\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T01:28:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne thing that kind of bugged me about ST.\u00A0\u00A0 They arrive on a planet, and their scanners detect something just happened, but what?\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 Ok... Warp far enough away that the event \u0027signal\u0027 can now be detected, and warp back.\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 They basically have a poor man\u0027s form of time travel, why not use it?\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T02:43:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711464\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575077313\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey basically have a poor man\u0027s form of time travel, why not use it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the same reason that some rare disease isn\u0027t easily cured using the medical supplies in the well-stocked sickbay, or the engine failure isn\u0027t solved by building a new part in the ship\u0027s machine shop or pulling a spare from the storeroom, or the emergency situation isn\u0027t handled by one of the multiple other starships in range of the problem area.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn short, it\u0027s because the crew and ship were exposed to a highly-charged field of plot radiation, and the intense ploticle residue tends to interfere with the common sense drive.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-11-30T02:45:28Z\u0022 title=\u002211/30/2019 02:45  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 30, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by razark\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T02:51:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711492\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575081834\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe engine failure isn\u0027t solved by building a new part in the ship\u0027s machine shop\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMachine shop?\u00A0\u00A0 Us machinists were put out of business with the invention of the fabricator.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T02:57:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711493\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575082299\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMachine shop?\u00A0\u00A0 Us machinists were put out of business with the invention of the fabricator.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do you fix the replicator when it needs a replacement frangedoodle and you can\u0027t replicate it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T03:07:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711498\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575082659\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do you fix the replicator when it needs a replacement frangedoodle and you can\u0027t replicate it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGo next door and ask to use their replicator.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T03:10:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711501\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575083264\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGo next door and ask to use their replicator.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee Star Fleet Command Memo #3, \u003Cem\u003EStarship Separation, Minimum Distances (in parsecs)\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T03:51:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711504\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575083457\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee Star Fleet Command Memo #3, \u003Cem\u003EStarship Separation, Minimum Distances (in parsecs)\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI meant the cabin next door.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI mean sure not every cabin had a replicator but more than 1 did, and if they are ALL broken you\u0027re likely in more trouble than having a broken replicator.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T06:26:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan the replicator replicate a ball of plasma?\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf so, they have an infinite source of energy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KSK","CreatedById":61025,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T07:36:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711501\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575083264\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGo next door and ask to use their replicator.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs that the 24th century equivalent of going round to borrow a cup of sugar? For the discerning starship crew member, etchings are probably back in vogue too - the real thing mind, none of your holo-replicated \u2018etchings\u2019.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711492\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575081834\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn short, it\u0027s because the crew and ship were exposed to a highly-charged field of plot radiation, and the intense ploticle residue tends to interfere with the common sense drive.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u201CEasy, Captain. I could resolve this problem by simply recalibrating the deflector to accept a phase sensible\u00A0pulse from the narrativium core. Unfortunately that\u2019s not an option.\u201D\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u201DMay I ask why not, Mr LaForge. I remind you that lives are at risk.\u201D\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u201DWriters Guild will go on strike, Captain. Again.\u201D\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T08:20:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711547\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575099399\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261025\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KSK\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n44 minutes ago, KSK said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u201CEasy, Captain. I could resolve this problem by simply recalibrating the deflector to accept a phase sensible\u00A0pulse from the narrativium core. Unfortunately that\u2019s not an option.\u201D\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u201DMay I ask why not, Mr LaForge. I remind you that lives are at risk.\u201D\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u201DWriters Guild will go on strike, Captain. Again.\u201D\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot the Galactica Maneuver!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Treveli","CreatedById":102579,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T12:59:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStar Trek has inspired so many scientists and inventors over the years, but if you look at the science and engineering used in the shows, it\u0027s like one of those \u0027the longer you look, the worse it gets\u0027 memes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T15:42:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot that weird the Star Trek science is, but the serious face they\u0027re doing about it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOrville tries to repair this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-11-30T15:43:36Z\u0022 title=\u002211/30/2019 03:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 30, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"\u03AD\u0137 \u03BD\u03AF\u013B\u013B\u03AC\u03AF\u03AE","CreatedById":197328,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T15:54:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRemember Star Wars?\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nNeed I explain?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExactly\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T16:06:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711672\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575129278\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197328\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022\u03AD\u0137 \u03BD\u03AF\u013B\u013B\u03AC\u03AF\u03AE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, \u03AD\u0137 \u03BD\u03AF\u013B\u013B\u03AC\u03AF\u03AE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRemember Star Wars?\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nNeed I explain?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExactly\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcept Star Wars never pretended to be sci-fi. It\u2019s classified as space opera or space fantasy. You can talk about the logical or plot inconsistencies, but this thread is about bad science in sci-fi\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: whoops, been so long since I actually\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eread\u00A0\u003C/em\u003Ethe thread title that I forgot this thread encompasses all fiction\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-11-30T16:59:13Z\u0022 title=\u002211/30/2019 04:59  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 30, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by StrandedonEarth\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"\u03AD\u0137 \u03BD\u03AF\u013B\u013B\u03AC\u03AF\u03AE","CreatedById":197328,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T16:12:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711679\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575130010\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcept Star Wars never pretended to be sci-fi. It\u2019s classified as space opera or space fantasy. You can talk about the logical or plot inconsistencies, but this thread is about bad science in sci-fi\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKk\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"\u03AD\u0137 \u03BD\u03AF\u013B\u013B\u03AC\u03AF\u03AE","CreatedById":197328,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T16:29:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk. I have a good one. Dunno if it\u2019s been said but remember Armageddon?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the scene with the shuttles, they go around in space like airplanes!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeing a kerbal player, I am triggered.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nForgive me if I got the wrong movie\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-11-30T16:30:13Z\u0022 title=\u002211/30/2019 04:30  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 30, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by \u03AD\u0137 \u03BD\u03AF\u013B\u013B\u03AC\u03AF\u03AE\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T16:36:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711679\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575130010\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis thread is about bad science in sci-fi\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNeither the thread title or \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E indicate this is only about sci-fi.\u00A0 There\u0027s plenty of bad science in all kinds of fiction.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}